00:37:25,130 --> 00:37:28,590
How can you insist it's love in court?

528
00:37:28,590 --> 00:37:31,020
But I thought it was love.

529
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:35,100
Anyhow, last week...

530
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,910
If we keep getting more work like this...

531
00:37:37,910 --> 00:37:43,260
I don't know if you'll even have time to go on dates with Attorney Han.

532
00:37:43,260 --> 00:37:46,580
Office Manager, how did you know I'm dating Attorney Han?

533
00:37:46,580 --> 00:37:49,920
If one of the associate attorneys leaves after hanging out together,

534
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:53,660
it's almost always they're together.

535
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:56,850
We were the only ones who thought we didn't get caught.

536
00:37:56,850 --> 00:37:59,450
You were saying you wanted to get married all the time.

537
00:37:59,450 --> 00:38:01,780
So, is it going well?

538
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:05,410
Well, I'm happy enough that I can be by her side.

539
00:38:05,410 --> 00:38:09,180
Oh, my. You're quite the romanticist, huh?

540
00:38:09,180 --> 00:38:12,810
Attorneys your age get so many calls from matchmakers.

541
00:38:12,810 --> 00:38:16,900
So, I thought you'd get married real soon.

542
00:38:16,900 --> 00:38:20,200
Marriage itself isn't what matters. Who you marry is more important.

543
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:23,200
Some couples barely last a year after getting married,

544
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,800
and some couples last decades while dating.

545
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:28,700
- Isn't it all like that?
 - Whoa.

546
00:38:31,570 --> 00:38:33,620
- Please take care.
 - Take care.

547
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:35,830
- I'll be in your care.
 - Thank you for your time.

548
00:38:35,830 --> 00:38:38,120
- Please take care.
 - Have a good day.

549
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:45,560
Jae Hui, you look so great in your uniform.

550
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:48,510
You're already in middle school.

551
00:38:49,700 --> 00:38:53,900
Are you concerned about something? Why did you want to see me?

552
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:58,690
My mom asked me

553
00:38:58,690 --> 00:39:01,590
what I think about starting to meet with Dad now.

554
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:04,330
I wanted to hear your thoughts.

555
00:39:04,330 --> 00:39:08,540
I felt you'd understand me since we're in the same boat.

556
00:39:15,990 --> 00:39:20,130
Well, this feels quite strange.

557
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:24,220
Is this like a meeting of children whose dads messed up?

558
00:39:24,220 --> 00:39:26,480
Yes, that's what this is.

559
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:29,690
Unless it happened to you, you'd never understand.

560
00:39:31,220 --> 00:39:33,530
He committed such a serious mistake.

561
00:39:33,530 --> 00:39:36,270
I don't want to forgive him easily.

562
00:39:42,130 --> 00:39:46,590
Jae Hui, this might not make sense to you,

563
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:54,500
but meeting and forgiving Dad might be two different issues.

564
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:56,950
How are they different?

565
00:39:56,950 --> 00:40:01,360
Meeting him and having a fun time like before while laughing...

566
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:04,230
That'd mean I forgave him.

567
00:40:06,060 --> 00:40:11,010
I completely understand you decided not to meet Dad because

568
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:13,410
you want to punish him.

569
00:40:13,410 --> 00:40:17,620
But you can't be punished as well, Jae Hui.

570
00:40:17,620 --> 00:40:20,230
You didn't do anything wrong.

571
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:25,850
You miss Dad, right?

572
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:35,990
I had thought I'd meet my dad after I forgave him.

573
00:40:37,070 --> 00:40:38,590
 Late Han Myeong Jong 

574
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:43,930
But I couldn't see him in the end.

575
00:40:47,110 --> 00:40:48,850
However...

576
00:40:49,750 --> 00:40:52,100
I was a bit regretful.

577
00:40:53,530 --> 00:40:56,730
I should've met him and resented him to his face.

578
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,910
- Could it be...
 - Yes.

579
00:41:01,310 --> 00:41:03,220
He passed away.

580
00:41:03,990 --> 00:41:06,530
It must've been tough for you.

581
00:41:10,710 --> 00:41:13,020
Just do as you wish, Jae Hui.

582
00:41:13,020 --> 00:41:15,000
Don't think too much about this.

583
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:19,830
If you need more time, you can meet him later.

584
00:41:22,450 --> 00:41:25,070
- Do you think my mom means it?
 - Huh?

585
00:41:25,070 --> 00:41:27,620
Telling me I can go meet Dad.

586
00:41:27,620 --> 00:41:30,090
Hey, of course!

587
00:41:30,090 --> 00:41:32,120
Of course, she sincerely means it.

588
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,640
I can guarantee you.

589
00:41:34,640 --> 00:41:37,590
Don't you think Mom's acting strong again?

590
00:41:37,590 --> 00:41:40,590
I'd be really sad if I were her.

591
00:41:42,690 --> 00:41:45,040
I know about that the best.

592
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:51,180
Your mom sincerely hopes you'll do as you wish more than anyone, Jae Hui.

593
00:41:54,030 --> 00:41:57,020
All right. It looks about done now.

594
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:00,150
It looks delicious. Shall we eat?

595
00:42:00,150 --> 00:42:02,270
- Your plate, please.
 - Okay.

596
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,200
Thank you, Attorney Han.

597
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:06,880
Yes.

598
00:42:14,590 --> 00:42:16,230
 Jae Hui's dad 

599
00:42:37,580 --> 00:42:40,260
- It's been a while.
 - Yes.

600
00:42:41,660 --> 00:42:45,810
Nothing's wrong with Jae Hui, right?

601
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:50,700
You fought so fiercely for custody back then.

602
00:42:50,700 --> 00:42:53,880
Why won't you mention visitations at all?

603
00:42:57,590 --> 00:43:03,430
I contemplate ten times a day whether I should contact Jae Hui first.

604
00:43:03,430 --> 00:43:08,780
But I figured it was only right to wait until Jae Hui reached out to me first.

605
00:43:08,780 --> 00:43:11,450
Jae Hui is 14 years old.

606
00:43:11,450 --> 00:43:15,670
Do you think Jae Hui can initiate what her dad has trouble doing?

607
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:24,460
Jae Hui misses her dad, too.

608
00:43:29,950 --> 00:43:31,750
Do you really think so?

609
00:43:31,750 --> 00:43:36,390
I contacted you first because you two might be distant for good at this rate.

610
00:43:37,650 --> 00:43:39,320
Thank you.

611
00:43:40,530 --> 00:43:44,290
Why don't you slowly start seeing her next week?

612
00:43:44,290 --> 00:43:47,780
I don't know if it's because some time passed,

613
00:43:47,780 --> 00:43:50,420
but Jae Hui laughs a lot lately.

614
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:57,800
Will Jae Hui want to see me?

615
00:43:57,800 --> 00:44:00,650
She probably can't forgive her dad.

616
00:44:00,650 --> 00:44:04,330
She might not be able to forgive you.

617
00:44:04,330 --> 00:44:11,190
But whether you're forgiven or not isn't important.

618
00:44:12,370 --> 00:44:16,930
What matters is Jae Hui shouldn't lose her dad.

619
00:44:30,410 --> 00:44:33,280
- Mom.
 - Hey, Jae Hui you're here.

620
00:44:36,150 --> 00:44:38,600
Give me one second. I'll finish up soon.

621
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:40,060
Okay.

622
00:44:42,700 --> 00:44:45,870
What did you talk about with Yu Ri?

623
00:44:45,870 --> 00:44:49,030
You don't need to know. It's a secret.

624
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:52,710
Jae Hui...

625
00:44:53,700 --> 00:44:59,000
I met your dad today, and he really misses you.

626
00:44:59,710 --> 00:45:04,620
Do you want to visit his house sometime next week?

627
00:45:06,230 --> 00:45:10,590
Just hang out with him as if nothing ever happened?

628
00:45:12,510 --> 00:45:14,930
You two were so close.

629
00:45:14,930 --> 00:45:19,740
It might be a little awkward at first,

630
00:45:19,740 --> 00:45:22,320
but you'll have fun in no time.

631
00:45:23,020 --> 00:45:25,200
You're able to do that?

632
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:32,700
- Can I be honest with you?
 - Yes.

633
00:45:37,540 --> 00:45:42,990
From now on, I'll always be honest with you.

634
00:45:46,690 --> 00:45:50,470
I don't think I can ever forgive him.

635
00:45:55,410 --> 00:46:01,530
But for you, whether you forgive him or not is up to you.

636
00:46:02,670 --> 00:46:07,290
Just meet him as your dad.

637
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:12,490
Because in this world he's your one and only dad.

