00:47:26,150 --> 00:47:29,010
By the way, Attorney Han...

653
00:47:29,010 --> 00:47:30,820
Yes.

654
00:47:30,820 --> 00:47:34,440
The case you were assigned yesterday...

655
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:40,340
The case of Mr. Kim Myeon Hwan and his five mistresses?

656
00:47:40,340 --> 00:47:42,360
Yes.

657
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:45,670
Is something wrong?

658
00:47:46,390 --> 00:47:51,170
I had a few questions while I was drafting the paperwork for that case.

659
00:47:51,170 --> 00:47:54,130
It's a case with five defendants,

660
00:47:54,130 --> 00:47:59,280
but is it right for one firm to represent all of them?

661
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:05,970
All six came to us because Defendant 1 said she'd pay everyone's legal fees

662
00:48:05,970 --> 00:48:08,940
because she felt bad for five other mistresses

663
00:48:08,940 --> 00:48:11,580
who received a complaint because of her.

664
00:48:11,580 --> 00:48:14,600
Yes, I'm aware of that, but...

665
00:48:17,390 --> 00:48:20,910
it feels ethically wrong to me.

666
00:48:22,690 --> 00:48:23,840
Sorry?

667
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:26,920
Each defendant might make a different claim

668
00:48:26,920 --> 00:48:29,570
and I have some doubts about

669
00:48:29,570 --> 00:48:32,370
whether it's appropriate for one office to handle a case

670
00:48:32,370 --> 00:48:34,810
where their interests are in direct conflict.

671
00:48:34,810 --> 00:48:37,850
My previous firm never handled a case this way.

672
00:48:37,850 --> 00:48:39,910
Your previous firm?

673
00:48:39,910 --> 00:48:43,860
Aren't you a rookie attorney?

674
00:48:43,860 --> 00:48:46,790
I worked as a paralegal at a law firm for five years

675
00:48:46,790 --> 00:48:49,130
before attending law school.

676
00:48:52,790 --> 00:48:56,430
Nonetheless, that matter should be handled by CEO Jeong.

677
00:48:56,430 --> 00:48:59,040
To win the cases that were assigned to you,

678
00:48:59,040 --> 00:49:02,710
you just need to diligently argue and prove your points.

679
00:49:04,020 --> 00:49:06,020
You can go now.

680
00:49:06,020 --> 00:49:07,690
Yes.

681
00:49:26,570 --> 00:49:31,000
Attorney Cha, we have a new hire.

682
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:35,310
But I'm totally lost as to how I should teach her.

683
00:49:35,310 --> 00:49:39,440
I'm not confident with questions like this.

684
00:49:39,440 --> 00:49:43,620
Didn't you hear two new hires quit before you started?

685
00:49:43,620 --> 00:49:46,560
You survived me because you're Han Yu Ri.

686
00:49:46,560 --> 00:49:49,360
What? What are you talking about?

687
00:49:49,360 --> 00:49:56,320
You taught me to like the divorce cases I once hated.

688
00:49:57,230 --> 00:50:02,470
Well, what kind of character is she? Lay it on me.

689
00:50:03,870 --> 00:50:06,610
 I look forward to the cases I'll be taking on. 

690
00:50:06,610 --> 00:50:09,080
 I'll do my best. 

691
00:50:09,080 --> 00:50:10,800
She's very clear-minded.

692
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:14,140
 It feels ethically wrong to me. 

693
00:50:14,140 --> 00:50:16,140
And she's ethical.

694
00:50:16,820 --> 00:50:19,700
She worked as a paralegal at a law firm for five years

695
00:50:19,700 --> 00:50:22,010
before becoming a lawyer.

696
00:50:22,010 --> 00:50:23,230
But...

697
00:50:23,230 --> 00:50:25,850
 I think I'll be fine using public transportation. 

698
00:50:25,850 --> 00:50:27,640
 I have some doubts. 

699
00:50:27,640 --> 00:50:31,330
 My previous firm never handled a case this way. 

700
00:50:31,330 --> 00:50:34,580
I guess you can say she has strong convictions?

701
00:50:34,580 --> 00:50:40,900
But that oddly angers me.

702
00:50:44,990 --> 00:50:46,720
That's totally Han Yu Ri.

703
00:50:46,720 --> 00:50:48,180
What?

704
00:50:51,320 --> 00:50:53,770
 I'm certain it's not an affair. 

705
00:50:53,770 --> 00:50:55,020
 I'll get it denied. 

706
00:50:55,020 --> 00:50:57,640
 The court mustn't overlook this, either. 

707
00:50:57,640 --> 00:50:59,730
 He needs to be taught a lesson. 

708
00:51:04,570 --> 00:51:06,350
You're right.

709
00:51:09,650 --> 00:51:12,050
I'm sorry for everything, Attorney Cha.

710
00:51:12,050 --> 00:51:15,400
This is what it means to be in someone else's shoes, huh?

711
00:51:20,710 --> 00:51:22,710
Well, I don't have any advice for you.

712
00:51:22,710 --> 00:51:25,350
Because I know you'll do better than me.

713
00:51:27,310 --> 00:51:31,090
Will I really be able to do well?

714
00:51:35,560 --> 00:51:37,860
Try giving her more cases.

715
00:51:37,860 --> 00:51:41,570
Because she'll eventually find the answer in the process.

716
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:46,280
To an attorney, cases are the medicine, right?

717
00:51:48,950 --> 00:51:50,720
Should I try that?

718
00:51:50,720 --> 00:51:53,680
I didn't think about that.

719
00:51:57,910 --> 00:51:59,300
Please take a look at this one.

720
00:51:59,300 --> 00:52:03,260
I just don't understand, so I don't know how I should respond.

721
00:52:04,020 --> 00:52:07,230
Are things going well with Attorney Jeon?

722
00:52:11,980 --> 00:52:13,890
Let me see your hand.

723
00:52:13,890 --> 00:52:15,440
My hand?

724
00:52:22,600 --> 00:52:24,460
What's this?

725
00:52:29,350 --> 00:52:32,550
Let's go on dates, eat delicious food,

726
00:52:32,550 --> 00:52:36,540
and watch movies together like we do now every day.

727
00:52:42,720 --> 00:52:46,990
Though I don't know the answer yet...

728
00:52:49,250 --> 00:52:51,050
Attorney Han.

729
00:52:52,170 --> 00:52:54,170
There's no answer.

730
00:52:54,170 --> 00:52:56,380
Marriage, remain single, and divorce...

731
00:52:56,380 --> 00:52:59,660
They're all choices.

732
00:52:59,660 --> 00:53:05,320
It's not that we need to make the right choice in itself.

733
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:09,980
It's putting in the effort to make that the right choice.

734
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:13,550
And if you've done your part by putting in the effort,

735
00:53:13,550 --> 00:53:17,670
you can make another choice without regretting it.

736
00:53:18,620 --> 00:53:21,980
Repeatedly making choices and taking responsibilities.

737
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:25,930
Isn't that what life is about?

738
00:53:33,660 --> 00:53:35,210
Yes.

739
00:53:35,710 --> 00:53:38,670
Regardless of what choice I make,

740
00:53:39,770 --> 00:53:45,590
I'll do my best to make that the right choice.

741
00:53:45,590 --> 00:53:47,580
Thank you, Attorney Cha.

